content.detailedDescription: Approximately 4:20 a.M. on october 5th 2015 i was alerted by my wife who was smoking a cigarette at the time.She called out a loud for me to come and see what she had seen up in the sky.At the time i was working in my shed.  i suffer from chronic back pain and could not sleep.  it is rare that we are up this early in the morning,  but not unusual for us to be looking at the sky.  this summer we had seen a lot of activity,  mostly just lights in the sky ,  the majority of them were probably satellites.On occasion we had seen this peculiar flashy thing, which is what my wife nicknamed it.The flashy thing was not what we saw this morning.Initially when she had called me out i thought she was teasing me so i was not taking her seriously .She told me that when she looked away to call me she had lost sight of it for a moment .  before i had  reached where she was i turned back towards the shed. but just as i reached the shed door ,she cried out there it is babe there it is what is that ?  i hurried back to where she was standing and pointing up at the sky.At first i did not see it then she stood behind me pointed her finger and told me to look straight down the line of her finger i finally saw it.By that time it was still very high in the sky like an aeroplane . three lights and absolutely no sound.I ran back to the shed and grabbed a pair of binoculars.As soon as i had returned it began descending.It was almost as though it knew where we were and that we were watching it.It descended to about approximately 1000 feet above us and banked towards us as though it was viewing us i handed her the binoculars and she said when she looked at it she couldn't tell what it was, so she handed me the binoculars and i took a look.It was very cold and fairly foggy at the time, but what i saw look like a  triangular hockey puck with three lights.The structure of the craft was very very dense or dark and the three lights did not pulse or flash they remained constant. it then leveled out and headed south towards national city , chula vista ,imperial beach, san isidro.As it got further and further away it did not seem to change altitude,  the entire time i would say approximately 1000 feet wasthe lowest altitude it flew .  we lost sight of it as it went past our home and into the distance. had our home been on the southern ridge and not on the northern ridge we would have probably been able to view it the entire time it headed south.  the entire event took approximately 3 to 4 minutes but it seemed like it took more like 20 minutes or more. strangest part of the sighting was that the craft seemed to expand or got bigger the further away it traveled. and  as it was heading southward i then called 9-1-1.  the 9-1-1 operator was a bit surprised  when i asked if any other calls had come in about a ufo.  she asked me if i felt in danger and then asked if i wanted to report a ufo. since the object came about 1000 feet above us and directly in the flight path of lindbergh field i said yes i want to report a ufo .  she then told me that this was not a life threatening event , so she  connected me to a non emergency line for the police departmnt who in turn told me a call brownfield or lindbergh field airport. since the police operator didn't seem like she was taking me seriously i decided not to make any more calls. after all of this my wife and i could not go back to sleep right away so we talked about it for the next hour or so then went back to bed .  since this sighting we haven't had but a few sightings and none of them were anything like this one.  mostly shooting stars or aircraft.  but definitely no ufos. my wife told me that when she first saw it , it looked like a comet or had a tail like a comet.  i think what we saw was a hologram. we've ufos are from another planet i think they're sinister like demonic and evil. honestly i believe ufos are the fallen angels that are described in the holy bible.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: At first very high ,then descended banked, then hovered, then levelled out, then flew south very very slowly

content.detailedDescription:
Visiting my mom for the thanksgiving holiday. i awoke shortly after 4:30 am without any reason. felt oddly restless; couldn't get back to sleep. got up to look out the window. observed a starless (possibly overcast?) sky and a white light in the nearby distance that seemed to wobble in a relatively stationary position.

this light alarmed me, because i'd witnessed a similar light that exhibited the same behavior in january of 2001. incidentally from that very same window.

the area behind my mother's house abuts a neighbor's yard who has very tall trees. the light (object) almost seemed to know that i was observing it and would move just enough to obscure itself behind a tree trunk. i'd change position, and shortly it would go back again. i had to keep at this tactic, going back and forth, in order to get a decent length of footage.

watching the video recently, i was kind of astonished by my whispered ramblings. i was mostly stating what i was seeing and trying to make sense of it, but at times i would go off on bizarre and somewhat incoherent tangents. i also didn't directly recall it at the time, but you can hear my mom's dog barking downstairs at some point. no one had stirred, but myself. and i'd been completely stationary with the exception of moving my camera's position throughout the sighting.

i would also like to state that after shooting this footage for about 20 minutes i found a pair of binoculars and wanted to get a better look at the light from the outside. i took my dog and my mom's dog with me to the back yard. looking through the binoculars i could discern that the one light i'd perceived with my unaided eyes was actually a row of 6 or 7 lights oriented at an awkward 12 to 15 degrees. it moved a lot slower and with less frequency at this point, though still at the same distance and location in the sky. i could also just barely see that the row of lights seemed to outline the object's apparent shape which was a disc or, perhaps cigar shaped. this was at about 5:10 am; still quite dark. i decided at that point to go back inside. i was going to check if it was still there before the sun came up, but i fell asleep.

i observed the same phenomena the following morning at approximately the same time. i awoke my mom this time to observe it with me. i think she was more annoyed that i'd awoken her than she was interested in observing it with me, to be honest.
content.summary: Observed a solitary white light that wobbled, but was overall stationary for over an hour in the eastern sky.

content.summary: Moving object(s) invisible to naked eye are visible in phone pics

content.detailedDescription: I have been taking pictures of three clouds now for about 1 1/2 months. my wife inspired me. she is a photographer and just opened up her on studio. she told me to look up,one day because i am missing out on a lot. i looked up and noticed a cloud with a shape of a bird. since then i have been taking lots of pictures of. louds. so on february 12,2016 between 1pm & 3pm i was at work and opened up my,window and noticed the bright sun and the clouds all around. so i got my phone camera and took many pictures. this lasted under 2 minutes.After that short period of time the clouds covered the sun and it was gone. when i first saw the object i thought it was on my lense or a glare from the sun. it was neither. it was an object that looked like an atom. it would rotate in many directions. it was in the clouds, behind the tree, near the sun. i begin doing some research on it. i found a picture like it on mufoncmc.Com. i would really like to get all the pictures authenticated. would you give me a certificate of authenticity? thank you very much. hope to hear from you soon.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Path with directional change,Path then hovering,Other
content.summary: Taking pictures of the sun & moon together. noticed there was a round object with white dots in the distance. i found a similar picture on your sight. .

content.detailedDescription: I was half way to work on 2/14/16 when a tremendous flash of blue light lit up the entire sky. woke me up for sure when another flash even more blue did the same thing without noise. thought it was an emp.  my co worker saw same thing driving in and has never seen anything like it. covered entire sky!
content.summary: Two bright flashes of blue lights illuminated clear sky at 4:30 am in morning covering entire sky

content.detailedDescription: I was delivering news papers at 4:30-5am in vacaville, ca. i was driving my car when a flash of light happened. i looked to my left and saw an object in the sky. i got out and tried to memorize every detail. after the event i drew it on a napkin and then painted it later. so it was big. i mean skyscraper big. it was far away but because it was so big it looked quite close. it was missile like with four wings on each end. it was simply a giant object in the sky. the lights came after i watched for about ten seconds. it was a huge flash of light. it suddenly had huge streak of light pointing toward the sky and a smaller light at the tip. the light was jagged. it was sharp. going outward. you can see in the painting i made. and this is where it gets weird. it then fades away. i figure the thing mustve been going so fast its image stayed when it was already gone. it faded like an old lightbulb when you turn off the switch. that's my guess anyway. i was excited to hear on the radio later that morning others saw the light too. and i cut out a newpaper clipping. they said in the paper it was a meteor. but what i saw had a shape. the whole thing lasted about a minute.
content.summary: While doing a paper route at 4:30am jan 17th 2013. flash of light ufo spotted. in news next day
